                            <comment id="15503813" author="yukim" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 15:48:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t it better to set DiskOptimizationStrategy in &lt;tt&gt;DatabaseDescriptor.clientInitialization&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15503881" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 16:14:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yukim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yukim&quot;&gt;yukim&lt;/a&gt; we could, I was just following what we do for the Partitioner.  Do you think we should we set that in there also?  But I think those things really only matter if someone is writing out sstables, so not sure where we want to put it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504027" author="yukim" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 17:08:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think putting it in DD is more future error proof, at least for DiskOptimizationStrategy, so you can just do clientInitialization and ready to go.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15504554" author="JIRAUSER308715" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2016 20:13:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yukim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yukim&quot;&gt;yukim&lt;/a&gt; ok, pushed a new version with everything moved into DD.clientInitialization()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15505787" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 20 Sep 2016 06:46:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is also fixed in the scope of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12450&quot; title=&quot;CQLSSTableWriter does not allow Update statement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-12450&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-12450&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (I faced the same problem as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jjordan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jjordan&quot;&gt;jjordan&lt;/a&gt;, although indirectly, had to fix the issue with &lt;tt&gt;UPDATE&lt;/tt&gt; statements and sstablewriter) &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
